result.execSummary:
The defendant Sara L. Doucette was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:06 am cases called. 14CM75, 14CM382, 15CM92, 15CM124, 14TR445 & 14TR446. Defendant Sara L. Doucette in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on record by ADA Anderson. Amended complaint on 14CM75 and Complaint on 15CM124 addressed. Attorney Szilagyi confirms receipt, waives further reading.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1-14CM75, No Contest to Count 2-14CM382, No Contest to Count 1-15CM92 & No Contest to Count 2-15CM124. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismissed outright Count 2 of 14CM75 and dismisses and reads-in Counts 1, 3, 4, 5 in 14CM382, Counts 2, 3, 4, & 5 in 15CM92, Counts 1, 3, 4, & 5 in 15CM124 and 14TR445 & 14TR446. No statement by the defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: 14CM75-50 days WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit. Credit for 15 days served. Sentence to begin forthwith. $1,694.00 to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. 24 mo DL revocation, 24 mo IID-effective today, OWI Assessment. 14CM382, 15CM92 & 15CM124: SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through,  Maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Terms of Agent. No Contact with A. Dunsirn (As named in the complaint of 15CM92). Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Court orders bonds on file to be applied, first to 14CM75 then to the balance of the counts. Appeal Rights Given. Statement by Attorney Szilagyi regarding a medical furlough. Statement by Court-Court grants a furlough for medical purposes from 6:00 pm April 21, 2015 and to report to the jail on June 19, 2015 no later than 8:00 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  No operation of any motor vehicles whatsoever.

Case called @ 1:06 p.m. Defendant Sara L. Doucette in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. ADA Anderson requesting $1000 Cash Bond. Atty Szilagyi requesting signature bond. Atty Szilagyi is requesting to have all pending matters scheduled for a plea/sentencing as soon as possible. Court orders $1000 Cash Bond.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for April 17, 2015 at 11:00 am.
